Manic Panic colours are so damn pretty and vibrant and usually even have a shine that's subtly multi-chrome, which is the prettiest thing ever BUT their bleach sucks balls.
There. I said it.
The reason is, that if you want a proper result you have to let a hairdresser do it or buy high quality, professional bleach.

I can recommend Manic Panic dyes to the moon and back, but please for the love of god use professional bleach from a hairdressing supply store or a hairdresser!

snippet.textDisplay:
Oh no Brad, that's not how chemistry works. An exothermic reaction releases heat, because it releases energy. Cooling it down doesn't stop the reaction, because the reaction isn't absorbing energy. That would be an endothermic reaction. Endothermic requires energy to be added (like heat). You could eventually overcome an exothermic reaction with cold, but it would take a lot more than a cold hair dryer to cause a problem for this particular reaction (*at 40 volume, I'd have to do some math to see if there's a concentration that could be overcome more readily). Heat speeds it up, but cold doesn't stop it.

- Chemist
